definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a dopamine receptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,4,6-trichlorophenol + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- 2,4-dichlorophenol + HCl.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  galactose (out) -eq- galactose(in).

Combining with advanced glycation end-products and transmitting the signal to initiate a change in cell activity. Advanced glycation end-products (AGEs) form from a series of chemical reactions after an initial glycation event (a non-enzymatic reaction between reducing sugars and free amino groups of proteins).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the RAGE receptor, the receptor for advanced glycation end-products.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + dUMP + NADPH + H+ -eq- dTMP + tetrahydrofolate + NADP+.
The expansion of a T cell population following activation by an antigenic stimulus.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with diazepam, one of the most widely used benzodiazepine drugs. It is used as an anti-anxiety-hypnotic agent and has the proprietary name Valium.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA, 4-aminobutyrate) receptor.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a phosphorylated serine residue within a protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a phosphorylated threonine residue within a protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with water (H2O).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with ice, water reduced to the solid state by cold temperature. It is a white or transparent colorless substance, crystalline, brittle, and viscoidal.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a toxin receptor, a receptor for substances that cause injury to living organisms.
Catalysis of the transfer of pyruvate, 2-oxopropanoate, from one side of the membrane to the other.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a cell adhesion molecule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a component of the extracellular matrix.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a cobalt (Co) ion.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a quaternary ammonium group, including glycine betaine, choline, carnitine and proline. A quaternary ammonium group is any compound that can be regarded as derived from ammonium hydroxide or an ammonium salt by replacement of all four hydrogen atoms of the NH4+ ion by organic groups.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the enzyme nitric-oxide synthase.
Catalysis of the joining of a metal ion to a molecule via a nitrogen-metal bond, with the concomitant hydrolysis of the diphosphate bond in ATP or a similar triphosphate.

label.value: ligase activity, forming nitrogen-metal bonds, forming coordination complexes

definition.value: Catalysis of the ligation of two substances via a nitrogen-metal bond, forming a coordination complex.
Catalysis of the reaction -  squalene -eq- hop-22(29)-ene.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with Hsp27 proteins, a lightweight heat shock protein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O-acetyl-L-homoserine + hydrogen sulfide -eq- homocysteine + acetate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the plus end of a microtubule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the minus end of a microtubule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an actin filament, also known as F-actin, a helical filamentous polymer of globular G-actin subunits.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any subunit of protein kinase A.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a mitogen-activated protein kinase.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a GTPase, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis of GTP.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a GDP-dissociation inhibitor protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a Rho GDP-dissociation inhibitor protein.
The cell cycle process in which a connection between chromatids assembles, indicating where an exchange of homologous segments has taken place by the crossing-over of non-sister chromatids.

Catalysis of the transfer of nucleic acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Nucleic acids are single or double-stranded polynucleotides involved in the storage, transmission and transfer of genetic information.
Catalysis of the transfer of RNA, ribonucleic acid, from one side of a membrane to the other.
Catalysis of the transfer of tRNA, transfer ribonucleic acid, from one side of a membrane to the other.
Catalysis of the transfer of DNA, deoxyribonucleic acid, from one side of a membrane to the other.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription during meiosis.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription during meiosis

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of transcription during meiosis.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription during meiosis

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription during meiosis.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with NF-kappaB, a transcription factor for eukaryotic RNA polymerase II promoters.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1,6)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in pullulan (a linear polymer of alpha-(1,6)-linked maltotriose units) and in amylopectin and glycogen, and the a- and b-limit dextrins of amylopectin and glycogen.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dADP + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- ADP + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dUDP + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- UDP + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dCDP + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- CDP + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dTTP + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- TTP + thioredoxin. Thioredoxin disulfide is the oxidized form of thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dCTP + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- CTP + thioredoxin. Thioredoxin disulfide is the oxidized form of thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosylcobinamide-GDP + alpha-ribazole -eq- GMP + adenosylcobalamin.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosylmethionine + 7-(aminomethyl)-7-deazaguanosine-tRNA -eq- adenine + methionine + epoxyqueuosine-tRNA. 7-(aminomethyl)-7-deazaguanosine-tRNA is also known as preQ1-tRNA, and epoxyqueuosine-tRNA as oQ-tRNA.
